itemDescription: British swimmer, Olympic athlete, Commonwealth Games gold medallist

wikipedia_page.main: Christine Lorraine Gosden (born 17 November 1939), also known by her married name Christine Parfect, is a female retired British swimmer.

response: The Sussex County Amateur Swimming Association or Sussex County ASA represents the interests of affiliated swimmers across Sussex.  Its first president was installed in 1895.  Brighton Swimming Club is the oldest swimming club in England, having been established in 1860.  Swimmers from Sussex include Iris Tanner, Christine Gosden, Rebecca Cooke and Gemma Spofforth.
